accd (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix handshake parser for real ACC client wire format (5 DriverInfo
    strings, 41-byte numeric block, full CarInfo with car customization).
  * Match Kunos welcome sequence order: 0x28, 0x36, 0x37.
  * Implement UDP keepalive response (0x14) and peer address learning.
  * Fix 0x28 large state response format (u8 prefix per f32 value).
  * Send 0x4e rating summary at disconnect instead of welcome.
  * Fix car dirt message ID: client sends 0x46, not 0x45.
  * Fix leaderboard car entry format (steam_id, short_name, first_name,
    last_name, car_model, cup_category).
  * Add probe test client for protocol capture and validation.

 -- Renaud Allard <renaud@allard.it>  Wed, 09 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +0200

accd (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Handshake validated against real Kunos accServer.exe 1.10.2.
  * Fix reject response to use 0x0c format (was 0x0b with 0xFFFF).
  * Fix accept header to include UDP port (was protocol version).
  * Fix welcome trailer strings to use u16-byte-len UTF-8 (was Format-A).
  * Fix CarInfo field order: raceNumber before carModel.
  * Parse DriverInfo and CarInfo from handshake request body.
  * Populate full welcome trailer with all Kunos sub-records.
  * Add post-accept 0x28, 0x36, 0x37, 0x4e welcome sequence.
  * Fix weather broadcast: correct scaling factors and grip level field.
  * Fix weather_init called from config with event.json values.
  * Preserve ambient/track temp across session reset.
  * Write results on session_advance for the last session.
  * Fix server-full off-by-one (nconns already includes connecting client).
  * Wire BanList into Server struct: enforce bans in handshake, persist on /ban.
  * Fix json_free for string-rooted documents.
  * Add systemd service to RPM package.
  * Harden systemd service with sandboxing directives.
  * Remove unused monitor_push_welcome_sequence.

 -- Renaud Allard <renaud@allard.it>  Wed, 09 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0200

accd (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix chat BOP argument parsing, /clear, /cleartp, track name bounds check.
  * Fix session standings sort to use session type instead of phase.
  * Add upper bound check on car_id in lap and sector handlers.
  * Move tick phase-tracking state into SessionState for correct session resets.
  * Fix monitor protocol to use actual session, weather, and config data.
  * Fix results JSON writer to escape strings and check fclose.
  * Fix bans_remove NULL dereference and bans_save silent write failure.
  * Enforce CONN_DISCONNECT: kicked/banned clients are now actually dropped.
  * Add SO_SNDTIMEO on client sockets to prevent slow clients from stalling.
  * Fix CI version detection for Fedora and Ubuntu, remove duplicate builds.

 -- Renaud Allard <renaud@allard.it>  Wed, 09 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200

